Build a simulation from a Python dict `input_dict` fully specifying entities.

Examples:

```pycon
>>> simulation_builder.build_from_entities({
    'persons': {'Javier': { 'salary': {'2018-11': 2000}}},
    'households': {'household': {'parents': ['Javier']}}
    })
```

Preprocess `input_dict` to explicit entities defined using the single-entity shortcut

Example:

```pycon
>>> simulation_builder.explicit_singular_entities(
    {'persons': {'Javier': {}, }, 'household': {'parents': ['Javier']}}
    )
>>> {'persons': {'Javier': {}}, 'households': {'household': {'parents': ['Javier']}}
```

Instantiate a ParameterNode either from a dict, (using `data`), or from a directory containing YAML files (using `directory_path`).

```
param str name

Name of the node, eg "taxes.some_tax".

param str directory_path

Directory containing YAML files describing the node.

param dict data

Object representing the parameter node. It usually has been extracted from a YAML file.

param str file_path

YAML file from which the  has been extracted from.
```

Instantiate a ParameterNode from a dict:

```pycon
>>> node = ParameterNode('basic_income', data = {
    'amount': {
      'values': {
        "2015-01-01": {'value': 550},
        "2016-01-01": {'value': 600}
        }
      },
    'min_age': {
      'values': {
        "2015-01-01": {'value': 25},
        "2016-01-01": {'value': 18}
        }
      },
    })
```

Instantiate a ParameterNode from a directory containing YAML parameter files:

```pycon
>>> node = ParameterNode('benefits', directory_path = '/path/to/country_package/parameters/benefits')
```
